latestPosts.caption:
Not everyone who smiles with you is your companion in the sight of Allah.
Sometimes, we think someone is our person that they’ll stay, stand beside us, understand us.
But slowly, distance grows. The calls fade. The promises don’t hold. And the friendship starts to feel one-sided.
True friendship in Islam is not about convenience. It’s about sincere du’a, gentle reminders, and standing together through deen and dunya.

If a bond didn’t last, maybe Allah removed it out of His mercy.
And maybe, just maybe, the friends who do stay those who remind you of Him are more than enough. 

For The Sake Of Allah 🤍

"The best of people are those who are most beneficial to others." – Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)

During this holy month of Ramadan,Let us increase acts of charity as an expression of gratitude to Allah and to help those in need. Allahu Akbar✨

Allah’s forgiveness is limitless and unconditional. Allah is“Al-Ghafoor” (The Most Forgiving) and “Ar-Rahman” (The Most Merciful), which signifies Allah’s infinite mercy and willingness to forgive anyone who sincerely repents. 

The Quran emphasizes that no matter how great the sins may be, if a person turns to Allah in repentance with a pure heart, Allah will forgive them. 

In Surah Az-Zumar (39:53), Allah says: 
Say, “O My servants who have harmed yourselves by your own actions, do not despair of Allah’s mercy. Indeed, Allah forgives all sins. Indeed, He is the Forgiving, the Merciful.”

Reminding all of you that you should never lose hope in seeking forgiveness, especially during blessed times like Ramadan when the doors of mercy are wide open.#
Also forgive others 🤍✨

Be thankful to الله. There’s always a reason to say Alhamdulillah✨🍉.
